Review Text:
Recently visited this place opposite dlf for dinner.
We had masala papad, tandoori roti, panner butter masala and aloo gobi.
Food was just decent, panner could have been softer and less elastic but the aloo gobi was fine. The ambience and service were good.
I would rate this restaurant as
Food - 2.5/5
Ambience - 3.5/5
Service - 3.5/5

I had been to this place for dinner. The place is very unhygenic. Wouldnt recommend this to anyone. We tried the Manchow soup and it had no taste. Food was ok! Could have been better. They did not have half of the things available with them. Prices are also high compared to others (in terms of taste and ambience)

Went with a bunch of frds to try. Tasty food. All food items are well cooked. Panner do pyaza and garlic naan are must try. Panner is very soft. Quantity is little less for that price. Little slow in service.
I have only visited once till now but I got loved with Gobhi Kulcha omg its superb in test and prices is 60 rupee. Aloo partha was also good. Like the packing style as well. Will try more items soon.

Been here for a lunch with a couple of business acquaintances. Service was slow and patchy. We ordered some butter rotis, kadai vegetable, veg pulao and Veg biriyani. The rotis were fine. As for the other dishes they were just passable. Nothing exceptional.

A place meant for north indian food lovers, i can guarantee that will not disappoint you. Must haves are there paranthas, paneer butter masala and paneer tikka . Very humble and efficient staff, listens to your minute details while placing order. Would love to visit this place with family again to try delicious food.
